A ReactJS web application to use in practice technologies learned in the whole semester.

# Get Started

If you want to run the project locally, you need to folllow the next steps:

1. **Clone the project**
   Clone the project from the GitHub repository [here](https://github.com/edman-cota/web-proyecto)

2. **Initialize the docker images**
   Navigate to the project root folder and run `docker-compose up`. This command will create the necessary docker images por next js, postgresql, vite js and adminer automatically and then it will create the docker container for the images created previously.
3. **Test the project**
   Now your can navigate to http://localhost:4000 using any browser to start using the app.

## Technologies

This software project was developed using some of the most recent web technologies:

| **Tech**                                      | **Description**                                           | **Learn more** |
| --------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- | -------------- |
| [React](http://facebook.github.io/react)      | Fast, composable client-side components                   | More...        |
| [Vite](https://vitejs.dev)                    | Vite Next Generation Frontend Tooling                     | More..         |
| [PostgreSQL](https://www.postgresql.org)      | The World's Most Advanced Open Source Relational Database | More...        |
| [pg](https://github.com/brianc/node-postgres) | Non-blocking PostgreSQL client for Node.js                | More...        |
| [Express](https://expressjs.com)              | Fast, unopinionated, minimalist web framework for Node.js | More...        |
| [nodemon](https://nodemon.io)                 | nodemon reload, automatically                             | More...        |
| [SASS](http://sass-lang.com)                  | Compiled CSS styles with variables, functions, and more   | More...        |
